 condition, Hennesy will refuse to have himself checked just to be by Alanis' side at all times, giving her priority over his studies.\n<small> '''Cast:''' [[Barbie Imperial]], [[Paulo Angeles]], Rosanna Roces, Isay Alvarez, Mike Lloren, Brace Arquiza, Jourdanne Castillo</small>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = Jersey\n| AltTitle        = \n| WrittenBy       = Bing Castro Villanueva\n| DirectedBy      = Darnel Joy R. Villaflor\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2019|01|19}}\n| Viewers         = 26.7%\n| ShortSummary    = Paul Desiderio is an aspiring athlete, son and student. His resiliency and dedication lead to greater height, when he became responsible for his team [[UP Fighting Maroons]], to lead to the Men's Basketball Finals of UAAP, after more than 3 decades.\n<small> '''Cast:''' [[Ronnie Alonte]], [[Loisa Andalio]], [[Ariel Rivera]], Bernadette Allyson, Jon Lucas, Noel Colet, Axel Torres, Tom Doromal, Miko Raval, [[Eda Nolan]], Y\u00f1igo Delen, Myle De Leon, Marco Masa, Ashley Sarmiento, Minco Fabregas</small>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| Title           = Pregnancy Test\n| AltTitle        = \n| DirectedBy      = FM Reyes\n| WrittenBy       = Akeem del Rosario\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2019|01|26}}\n| Viewers         = 27.7%\n| ShortSummary    = \n<small> '''Cast:''' [[Ritz Azul]], [[Ahron Villena]], [[Irma Adlawan]], [[Lito Pimentel]], Arlene Muhlach, [[Carlos Morales (actor) | Carlos Morales]], [[Victor Silayan]], [[Louise Abuel]], [[Belle Mariano]], [[Jef Gaitan]], Kirst Viray, Ben Isaac</small>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 4\n| Title               = Family Portrait\n| AltTitle            = \n| DirectedBy          = Nuel C. Naval\n| WrittenBy           = Joan Habana\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{start date|2019|02|02}}\n| Viewers             = 22.0%\n| ShortSummary        = \n<small> '''Cast:''' [[Christopher de Leon]], [[Sandy Andolong]], Sandino Martin, [[Danita Paner]], [[Alexa Ilacad]], Michelle Vito, [[Cindy Miranda]], Ana Abad Santos, [[James Blanco]], [[Claire Ruiz]], Raikko Mateo</small>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| Title           = [[Steak (Maalaala Mo Kaya)|Steak]]\n| AltTitle        = \n| DirectedBy      = Elfren Vibar\n| WrittenBy       = Mae Rose Balanay\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2019|02|09}}\n| Viewers         = 25.0%\n| ShortSummary    = [[Bong Go|Christopher \"Bong\" Go]] had hatred with his father due to his principles. But, his luck changed when he became the Assistant of then-Mayor and eventually [[President of the Philippines]] [[Rodrigo Duterte]]. His loyalty to his boss lead him to what he had become. But, there is one thing that he had to accomplish, to be a family man.\n<small> '''Cast:''' [[Joseph Marco]], [[Phillip Salvador]], [[Meg Imperial]], [[Nonie Buencamino]], [[Shamaine Centenera-Buencamino]], Andre Garcia, Raine Salamante, Clarence Delgado, Marc Santiago, [[CX Navarro]], [[Leo Martinez]]</small>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| Title           = White Ribbon\n| AltTitle        = \n| DirectedBy      = Raymund B. Ocampo\n| WrittenBy       = Mary Rose Colindres\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2019|02|16}}\n| Viewers         = 27.2%\n| ShortSummary    = [[Moira dela Torre]] had always longed for a complete and happy family and it broke her when her dreams did not come true. She tried to find herself and her purpose in different ways. She even joined The Voice and entered showbiz. She finally felt complete when she surrendered her life to her faith. From then, things started falling into place for her including finding true unconditional love in her bestfriend of seven years, Jason (Kiko). How was Moira able to find herself amidst her troubled heart? How did Moira and Jason's love story begin?\n<small> '''Cast:''' [[Janella Salvador]], [[Kiko Estrada]]</small>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| Title           = Lotion\n| AltTitle        = \n| DirectedBy      = Eduardo Roy Jr.\n| WrittenBy       = Bing Castro-Villanueva\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2019|02|23}}\n| Viewers         = 26.1%\n| ShortSummary    = Bernadette was born with dark, rough skin, bulging eyes and a facial deformity. Her mother, Jona believes it is a curse on their family, but will still try her best to accept the child. Due to her mother's hesitation to accept her, Bernadette will feel unloved, and try to seek affection from other people. Until one day she gets pregnant but will be left hanging by the man whom she thought had truly loved her. Who will help Bernadette in her time of need? Where will she be able to find the love she is desperately searching for?\n<small> '''Cast:''' Mary Joy Apostol, [[Meryll Soriano]], Arnold Reyes, Marc Acueza, [[Teejay Marquez]], [[Patrick Sugui]], Miel Espinoza, Karla Pambid, [[Lance Lucido]], Teetin Villanueva, [[Yesha Camile]], Krystal Mejes</small>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 8\n| Title               = Mansanas\n| AltTitle            = Apple\n| DirectedBy          = Carlo Po Artillaga\n| WrittenBy           = Akeem Del Rosario\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{start date|2019|03|02}}\n| Viewers             = 30%\n| ShortSummary        = Emman has always wanted to finish his studies but because of the hardships in life, he has opted to work instead in a bakery. There, he meets the woman of his dreams, Maricar (Denise), who also happens to be his boss. Maricar's family does not like Emman for her because they don't think he will be able to provide for her future as he did not finish his studies. But they will fight for their love as Emman works hard to achieve his dreams of finishing school and to prove himself to Marica's parents. How will Emman be able to overcome the challenges in his life and the obstacles in his relationship with Maricar?\n<small> '''Cast:''' [[Joem Bascon]], [[Denise Laurel]], [[Tetchie Agbayani]], [[Xia Vigor]], Levi Ignacio, Zeppi Borromeo, Micah Mu\u00f1oz, Kaiser Boado, Vernon Hanwell</small>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 9\n| Title               = Painting\n| AltTitle            = \n| DirectedBy          = Barry Gonzales\n| WrittenBy           = Joan Habana\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{start date|2019|03|09}}\n| Viewers             = 25.8%\n| ShortSummary        = Ancel has always been insecure of her looks because of her heavy weight set. She is often used to connect suitors to her beautiful and thin friends. That will all change when she meets Mark, the popular basketball player in their school who will fall head over heels in love with her despite her weight and insecurities. Will their relationship stay strong and be able to withstand the judgment of other people?\n<small> '''Cast:''' [[Elisse Joson]], Kit Thompson, [[Epi Quizon]], [[Bernard Palanca]], Cheska I\u00f1igo, Joj Agpangan, Alexa Miro, Patty Mendoza, Yasmyne Suarez</small>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 10\n| Title               = Black Belt\n| AltTitle            = \n| DirectedBy          = Jerome Pobocan\n| WrittenBy           = Dickson Comia\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{start date|2019|03|16}}\n| Viewers             = 29.7%\n| ShortSummary        = Ramon grew up in a poor community in Bicol and was abandoned by his father at an early age. From the province, he went to Manila hoping to give his family a better future and to be able to finish his studies. One day, his professor encouraged him to try Karate to earn a scholarship. His hard work paid off when a Singaporean Kyokushin Karate trainer, Sensei Steven (Atoy Co), discovered him and helped him finish high school and become a Karate champion. As his dreams slowly turned to his favor, another setback arose when his girlfriend got pregnant and eventually betrayed him. How did he survive after all of the challenges in his life? What inspired him to enter the MMA scene?\n<small> '''Cast:''' [[JM De Guzman]], Allan Paule, Glenda Garcia, [[Mon Confiado]], [[Atoy Co]], Erin Ocampo, [[Japoy Lizardo]], Y\