ya episodes}}\n[[Category:2019 Philippine television seasons]]\n[[Category:Maalaala Mo Kaya]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{main|List of Maalaala Mo Kaya episodes}}\n{{Infobox television season\n| image            = \n| season_number    = 27\n| bgcolour         = #FFC0CB\n| caption          = \n|starring          = [[Charo Santos]]\n| country          = Philippines\n| network          = [[ABS-CBN]]\n| first_aired      = {{start date|2019|01|12}}\n| last_aired       = {{end date|2019|12|28}}\n| num_episodes     = 47\n| episode_list     = List of Maalaala Mo Kaya episodes\n| image_alt        = \n| released         = \n| prev_season      = [[Maalaala Mo Kaya (season 26)|season 26]]\n| next_season      =  [[Maalaala Mo Kaya (season 28)|season 28]]\n}} \n\n'''''[[Maalaala Mo Kaya]]''''' ({{translation|Would you remember?}}; abbreviated '''''MMK'''''), also known as '''''Memories''''' in English, is a [[Filipino people|Filipino]] [[television series]], which was first aired on May 15, 1991. MMK is the longest-running drama anthology on [[Television in the Philippines|Philippine television]].\n\n== Episodes ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"margin: auto; width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#778899; color:#fff;\"| #\n! style=\"background:#778899; color:#fff;\"| Episode title\n! style=\"background:#778899; color:#fff;\"| Directed by\n! style=\"background:#778899; color:#fff;\"| Written by\n! style=\"background:#778899; color:#fff;\"| Original air date\n! style=\"background:#778899; color:#fff;\"| Ratings\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = Journal\n| AltTitle        = \n| WrittenBy       = Mary Rose Colindres\n| DirectedBy      = [[Theodore Boborol]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2019|01|12}}\n| Viewers         = 25.4%\n| ShortSummary    = Follow the story of couple Alanis and Hennesy, who will fight for their love in spite of their health conditions: Alanis has a chronic kidney disease while Paolo h